# Rule Testing Patterns

Test your rules to catch drift early.

## What to test

### Structure tests

For every `.mdc` file:

- [ ] Has frontmatter (`--- ... ---`)
- [ ] Has `description:` field
- [ ] Has `alwaysApply:` field
- [ ] Has `priority:` field
- [ ] Has `tags:` field
- [ ] Has `# Title` heading
- [ ] Has `##` subsections

### Content tests

- [ ] `description` is one sentence
- [ ] `alwaysApply` is boolean
- [ ] Rules are actionable (no vague language)
- [ ] Examples are realistic
- [ ] No broken links to other files

### Quality tests

- [ ] File is under 150 lines
- [ ] Language matches the project's tone
- [ ] Sections follow consistent structure
- [ ] Code blocks have language tags

## How to run

```bash
npm run validate
```

This runs `scripts/validate-skills.mjs` which checks all skills and rule files.

## When to test

- After creating a new rule
- After modifying an existing rule
- Before committing
- During code review

## Fixing failures

| Failure | Fix |
|---|---|
| Missing frontmatter | Add proper YAML frontmatter |
| Missing description | Add one-sentence description |
| File too long | Split into smaller rules |
| Broken link | Update path to target file |
